<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Sources' Optimistic Over 'Arafat's Remarks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0803053194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0500 GMT 8 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0803053194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Political sources in Jerusalem say the conditions 
are not right yet for renewing negotiations with the PLO. At 
the same time, the sources told Qol Yisra'el's political affairs 
correspondent that Yasir 'Arafat's remarks in Cairo to senior 
Israeli officials leaves grounds for optimism. The contacts 
would enable further exchanges between the parties. Attending 
the meeting with 'Arafat in Cairo were Prime Minister Rabin's 
political adviser Jacques Neriya, his deputy military secretary, 
Lieutenant Colonel 'Amos Gil'ad, and Israel's Ambassador David 
Sultan. Premier Rabin was briefed last night on the contacts 
and will today hold consultations on what transpired in Cairo. 
'Arafat has meanwhile returned to Tunis. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

