<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Diplomatic Sources on Four-Point Peace Compromise </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0403181994 Tel Aviv 'AL HAMISHMAR in Hebrew 4 Mar 94 pp 1, 
6 </F>

<F P=103> TA0403181994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv 'AL HAMISHMAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Pinhas 'Inbari, Pe'erli Shahar, Aharon Klein, and </F>
Natan Gutman in Washington] 
  [Excerpt] Diplomatic sources in Israel reported that 
international elements are trying to work out a four-point 
compromise permitting the resumption of the Washington talks: 
Israel will speed up the process of disarming the dangerous 
settlers; Israel will move "settlement points" in the heart of 
Arab towns -- Hebron, Nabulus, and Jericho, as well as Netzarim; 
the UN Relief and Works Agency will be strengthened and Israel 
will recognize its presence outside the refugee camps and its 
status as an observer, which it took on during the intifadah to 
Israel's dismay; and Israel will agree to release more 
Palestinian prisoners beyond the 1,000 already freed. 
  The sources said that if all the sides agree to this wording 
it will be possible to renew the talks in Washington in 10 days. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

