<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Knesset Member Katz Receives Letter From 'Arafat </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0403112694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1000 GMT 4 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0403112694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Knesset Member Yosi Katz today received a letter 
from Yasir 'Arafat in which he expresses the hope that all the 
forces working for peace in Israel will participate in adopting 
practical measures to block the activities of the settlers, 
something that will make it possible to quickly implement the 
Declaration of Principles agreement. 
  Our correspondent Yo'el Nir reports that 'Arafat sent the 
letter in response to a cable from Knesset Member Katz in which 
he called on him to demonstrate leadership and overcome those 
who are trying to torpedo the peace process. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

