<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia's Ivanov Meets Rabin, Views Peace Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0303120394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1100 GMT 3 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0303120394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Yegor Ivanov says 
all sides should return to the Middle East peace talks without 
preconditions. Ivanov met with Prime Minister Rabin this 
morning at the Defense Ministry in Tel Aviv. Dani Gur-Arye 
reports: 
  Prime Minister Rabin and Deputy Foreign Minister Ivanov met 
for almost an hour in Tel Aviv. Later Ivanov, who recently met 
with PLO leader Yasir 'Arafat, told reporters most meetings 
centered on ways to renew the peace talks: 
  [Begin Ivanov recording; Ivanov speaks in Russian with 
superimposed translation into English] In this new situation 
none of the sides can set preconditions. The best solution is 
for all sides to return promptly to the talks. [end recording] 
  Ivanov was asked about criticism Rabin levelled recently at 
Russia over its attempt to mediate between the sides 
independently of the United States. 
  [Begin Ivanov recording] Russia and the United States are 
the 
co-sponsors of the Middle East process, and there are ground 
rules for cooperation. With that, each of the co-sponsors is 
free to take its own initiatives as long as the goal is to 
further the peace talks. [end recording] 
  Ivanov said he is convinced Russia can help bring the sides 
back together. 

</TEXT>

