<H3> <TI>   Islamic Jihad Cell Uncovered in North </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0403152794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1400 GMT 4 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0403152794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An Islamic Jihad cell, which tried to obtain 
weapons, among other things, was uncovered in northern Israel, 
our correspondent Yo'av Aviv reports. He says the cell was 
uncovered by the Shin Bet and the Bureau for Special Tasks in 
Ha'amaqim District. Cell members come from Janin and Umm 
al-Fahm. An Umm al-Fahm resident assisted the cell members in 
forming ties with arms dealers in the Israeli underworld and 
obtaining information on Israel. The cell leaders were arrested 
and their interrogation is continuing. 

</TEXT>

