<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Both Sides To Cooperate in Conflict </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0603113294 Tehran IRNA in English 1045 GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0603113294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, March, 6, IRNA -- Iran and Russia here 
Saturday agreed to cooperate for peaceful settlement of current 
disputes in the Republic of Tajikistan. The agreement was 
reached by Iran's Deputy Foreign Minister Mahmud Va'ezi and his 
Russian counterpart Anatoliy Adamishin, currently here to 
discuss regional and bilateral issues with Iranian officials. 
  Adamishin, who arrived here last Friday, said that there was 
proper grounds for Tehran-Moscow cooperation to resolve 
Tajikistan disputes. Referring to the endeavors made by the 
Islamic Republic to bring an end to the disputes, Va'ezi 
reiterated that Iran, like before, would continue efforts to 
establish a just peace in Tajikistan. 
  Any effort should be based on existing realities inside 
Tajikistan and be aimed at resolving people's problems, Va'ezi 
added, stressing that the best way to this end was formation of 
a government able to materialize national aspirations of the 
Tajik people. 
  Adamishin is also expected to hold official talks with Tajik 
government's opposition leaders. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

