<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Urges Democracy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0603172194 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0603172194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Within the framework of national reconciliation plan 
in Tajikistan, the first round of talks between the leaders of 
Tajikistan's Islamic and national groups opposed to the present 
government in Tajikistan and the first deputy foreign minister 
of Russia, Anatoliy Adamishin, began in Tehran today. 
  During these talks the leaders of the opposition groups 
explained their views on ways of restoring tranquillity and 
security in that country and stressed the need for establishment 
of democracy by involving all the forces of Tajikistan in 
running the country's affairs. 
  These talks are taking place with approval of the present 
government in Tajikistan, UN support, and cooperation of the 
Islamic Republic of Iran [IRI]. The IRI, which is striving to 
restore peace in combination with tranquillity and stability in 
Tajikistan, stressed from the beginning that the military option 
cannot solve this country's political and economic problems; and 
the only way of resolving Tajikistan's difficulties is 
establishment of national reconciliation government. 

</TEXT>

