<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<H3> <TI>   GCC Oil Ministers Begin Meeting in Jeddah </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0503212394 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 2040 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0503212394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Jeddah, 5 Mar -- The oil ministers of the GCC 
[Gulf Cooperation Council] states have begun the meetings of 
their 19th session here tonight under the chairmanship of Hisham 
Nazir, the Saudi minister for petroleum and mineral resources. 
  At the beginning of the one-day meeting, the Saudi minister 
for petroleum and mineral resources gave a speech in which he 
stressed the importance of cooperation among GCC members in 
order to achieve their interests. 
  Minister Nazir expressed the hope that the meeting would 
produce decisions in order to solve some "outstanding" matters. 
  During the meeting the ministers are due to hear a report 
from Sa'id al-Shanfari, the Omani minister for petroleum and 
minerals, on the results of his contacts with non-OPEC 
oil-producing countries to urge them to respond to the 
initiative of the GCC leaders regarding their countries' 
readiness to reduce their oil production on condition that the 
non-OPEC oil-producing countries took a similar step. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-13022 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes045_l_94009" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-045 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  8 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   IDF: No Reserve Duty for Settlers on Detention </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0503194794 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1900 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0503194794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1900 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The IDF [Israel Defense Forces] has decided that 
settlers who received orders restricting their movements or 
administrative detention orders and have had their IDF weapons 
taken away, will not serve in their reserve units and will not 
be called up for reserve duty for the time being, the IDF 
spokesman said tonight. 
  The parents of Eyal Moqed, one of the administrative 
detainees, announced that they would demonstrate tonight outside 
the Hasharon Prison demanding that their son be presented 
immediately before a judge as is the practice in administrative 
detentions cases of any Israeli citizen. Shmu'el Ben-Ishay of 
Qiryat Arba', who was detained for three months under an 
administrative order, is also incarcerated in Hasharon Prison, 
and the High Court of Justice will consider the legality of his 
detention this week. 

</TEXT>

