<H3> <TI>   New Presidency Appointments; Further Amnesty Possible </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0803114394 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 8 Mar 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM0803114394 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] ALgiers, AL-HAYAH -- AL-HAYAH has learned that 
new administrative appointments were made the day before 
yesterday in the presidency. Djaballah Belkacem (former member 
of the local supreme information council) has been appointed as 
director of information in the presidency, succeeding Mohamed 
Zehani, who has been appointed as the former's deputy for public 
relations. Mr. Ben Abbo, former presidential adviser, has been 
appointed as director general of the department. 
  Well-informed Algerian sources have said that further 
appointments will be made in the next few days at the 
presidency, government, and the economic-social council level. 
  Presidency circles have begun to consider a number of 
measures to ease the severity of the tension the country has 
been experiencing for a week. The sources pointed to the 
possibility a general amnesty being issued for a new group of 
detainees in the coming few days and the curfew imposed on 
central provinces lifted on the occasion of the blessed 'Id 
al-Fitr. [passage omitted] 

