<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   General Warns of Military Confrontation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0903094494 Amman AL-DUSTUR in Arabic 9 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN0903094494 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-DUSTUR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Hamdan al-Hajj] </F>
  [Text] Brigadier General Mujahid Abu-Shawarib, Yemeni 
deputy prime minister, has called on President 'Ali 'Abdallah 
Salih and his deputy 'Ali Salim al-Bid to be rational and to 
give utmost priority to the interests of the homeland and 
nation. He urged them to stop making mistakes in order to save 
Yemen from the bad consequences of letting things continue as 
they are. 
  In a telephone interview with AL-DUSTUR, Abu-Shawarib said 
that after all the efforts that have been made, he believes 
there are people working for separation. Based on this belief, 
he said that he had resigned from the dialogue committee because 
he does not want to suffer the condemnation of history, because 
all those who contribute to the foiling of unity will be 
condemned by history. He said Yemen will endure, and the faith 
of Yemenis in their unity will continue, and individuals will be 
gone, sooner or later. 
  Brigadier General Abu-Shawarib expressed pessimism about 
Yemen's foreseeable future, because the president and his 
deputy, and the People's Congress Party and the Yemeni Socialist 
party, continue making mistakes visible to local, regional, and 
international public opinion. Each party is trying to show it 
is eager to maintain unity, but this is not the real situation, 
he and his colleagues in the dialogue committee have concluded. 
  Brigadier General Abu-Shawarib expected something to happen 
in the near future unless reason prevails. He said it is a 
matter of time. If recriminations continue, they will lead to a 
military confrontation, and Yemeni unity will be the scapegoat. 
  He prayed to God to save Yemen from the plots of its enemies 
inside and outside, especially since the situation has reached 
the point in which reform is useless unless things are returned 
to normalcy, and living consciences give priority to Yemen and 
the Yemeni interest. 
  Brigadier General Abu-Shawarib highly valued the role played 
by His Majesty King Husayn toward the signing of the document of 
pledge and accord, and his eagerness to maintain the Yemeni's 
unity and fraternal spirit, and his desire to do all he can to 
preserve Yemeni unity. At the same time, he expressed 
appreciation of the Omani role in this field, and hoped that 
other Arab parties will play good roles that serve the interests 
of Yemen and the Yemenis. 
  Brigadier General Abu-Shawarib hoped that the Yemeni 
president and his deputy will return to the right path and do 
what is for the good of Yemen in order to save their country 
from dangers known only to God. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

