<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Libya's al-Kharrubi, Arab League Team Depart Sanaa </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0803211994 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0803211994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brother Colonel Mustafa al-Kharrubi, member of the 
Revolution Command Council and inspector general in the Libyan 
Arab Jamahiriyah, left Sanaa today following a three-day visit 
to our country. During his visit he conveyed messages from 
brother Libyan leader Colonel Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi to both 
President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and Vice President 'Ali 'Abdallah 
Salih. The messages deal with issues of joint interest to both 
fraternal countries and with current developments in our country. 
  He was seen off by Deputy Prime Minister 'Abd-al-Wahhab 
al-Anisi, and a number of officials. 
  An Arab League delegation, led by Staff Major General 
Muhammad Sa'id Bayraqdar, assistant secretary general and head 
of the Arab League's Department for Military Affairs, also left 
Sanaa today following a visit of several days to our country. 
  In a statement to the Yemeni News Agency, SABA', the league 
military official said that he met with officials in our country 
and discussed with them ways to end the military repercussions 
that have recently prevailed in the country. He described his 
visit to our country as positive and successful, and that he had 
formed a good impression. He also wished Yemen and the Yemeni 
people progress and prosperity. 
  He was seen off by brother Yahya al-Shami, deputy head of 
the 
Arab Homeland Department at the Yemeni Foreign Ministry, and a 
representative of the Presidential Council's Protocol Department. 

</TEXT>

