<H3> <TI>   Deputy Criticizes U.S. Ambassador's Activities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0803140594 Shanayh Voice of the Mountain in Arabic 1230 
GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0803140594 </F>
<F P=104>  Shanayh Voice of the Mountain </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Chamber of Deputies held a plenary session 
today. [passage omitted] 
  Deputy 'Ali 'Ammar assailed the U.S. ambassador's 
interference in Lebanon's internal affairs. He said: Before 
the two massacres were committed [Hebron killings and Lebanese 
church explosion], it was expected that something would happen 
in Lebanon, as shown by the U.S. ambassador's statements. The 
ambassador's interference goes beyond all international norms 
and constitutes intervention in Lebanese internal affairs like 
between a victim and a murderer. He also provokes certain agents 
and symbols to foment sedition. Deputy 'Ammar added: It is 
time that the pertinent authorities stopped responding to the 
U.S. intentions that seek to cause sedition among the Lebanese 
people. 
  He asked the Chamber of Deputies to adopt a stand denouncing 
the U.S. envoy's behavior. [passage omitted] 
  [Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic at 1235 GMT on 8 March 
adds: 
"Deputy 'Ali 'Ammar called U.S. Ambassador Mark Hambley the 
ambassador of filth [safir al-danas]. He described his movements 
as suspicious and as going beyond diplomatic limits. He said 
that the ambassador equates victims and criminals."] 

</TEXT>

