<H3> <TI>   Tajik Opposition Leader Comments on Situation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0903091794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0430 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0903091794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The head of the Tajik opposition delegation has 
stressed that the opposition believes that an impartial interim 
government should assume power and hold free elections to end 
the current crisis. 
  Speaking in an interview in Tehran yesterday, Akbar 
Turjanzadeh said: A popular rule that the Tajik people want 
should be established through free elections. 
  He described the role played by the Islamic Republic of Iran 
in solving the Tajikistan crisis as noteworthy and said: During 
our talks in Tehran with the Russian Government delegation, it 
was agreed that the first round of talks for the solution of the 
Tajikistan crisis be held in Moscow with the participation of 
representatives from the Islamic Republic of Iran, Pakistan, 
Afghanistan, and the United Nations. 
  In conclusion, he called for the active role of the Islamic 
Conference Organization in solving the Tajikistan crisis. 

