<H3> <TI>   PLO's 'Abbas Arrives, To Discuss Resuming Talks </TI></H3>
<H4>   Musa, 'Abbas To Discuss Contacts </H4>
<F P=102> NC0803204094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2000 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0803204094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 8 Mar (MENA)--PLO Executive Committee member 
Mahmud 'Abbas, also known as Abu-Mazin, arrived in Cairo this 
evening on a two-day visit to Egypt. 
  Arriving, he said he will meet later tonight with Foreign 
Minister 'Amr Musa to discuss the latest Palestinian-Israeli 
contacts and the UN Security Council debate and to search for a 
suitable solution to resume talks with the Israelis to implement 
the Gaza-Jericho Agreement. 
  Abu-Mazin said the Palestinian leadership is always eager 
for 
contacts and consultations with Egypt as a full partner to the 
negotiations. 

</TEXT>

