<H3> <TI>   PLO's 'Abbas Arrives, To Discuss Resuming Talks </TI></H3>
<H4>   Palestinian Issue Reviewed </H4>
<F P=102> NC0803220994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2150 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0803220994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 8 Mar (MENA)--Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa 
tonight met PLO Executive Committee member Mahmud 'Abbas, who 
arrived in Cairo earlier today. 
  The meeting, which was attended by Palestinian Ambassador in 
Cairo Sa'id Kamal and Fatah representative Zuhdi al-Qidrah, 
reviewed developments in the Palestinian issue. 
  The talks followed Palestinian president Yasir 'Arafat's 
discussions in Cairo. They evaluated the peace process in light 
of the recent developments and the impact of the al-Ibrahimi 
Mosque massacre on the peace march. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

