<DOCNO> FBIS3-13071 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes046_c_94004" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-046 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  9 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO's 'Abbas Arrives, To Discuss Resuming Talks </TI></H3>
<H4>   'Abbas Comments on Discussions </H4>
<F P=102> NC0903065494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2230 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0903065494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 8 Mar (MENA)--PLO Executive Committee Member 
Mahmud 'Abbas has said that he discussed with Foreign Minister 
'Amr Musa the crisis that the Palestinian-Israeli peace process 
is now experiencing as a result of the Hebron massacre. 
  He said after his meeting with the foreign minister today 
that they also discussed the Palestinian demands to resolve the 
crisis, both a UN Security Council resolution and measures that 
the Israeli Government needs to take to prevent the recurrence 
of the massacre. 
  He said the two sides also discussed cooperation between 
Egypt and the PLO to achieve the best results. 
  On the possibility of a summit meeting between Palestinian 
President Yasir 'Arafat and Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq 
Rabin, 'Abbas said such a meeting is out of the question before 
certain measures have been taken: the issuance of a Security 
Council resolution and adoption of specific Israeli positions to 
handle the crisis resulting from the massacre. 
  On the Palestinian proposals presented to Rabin, 'Abbas said 
the PLO has not yet received an Israeli reply. 
  He said the PLO presented specific and known proposals that 
can be summed up by the following questions: How can the 
Palestinian people be protected and how can another Hebron 
massacre be prevented? We have not yet received a reply from 
the Israeli Government, he said. 
  What is needed, 'Abbas asserted, is UN-recognized 
international observers to protect the Palestinians. 

</TEXT>

