<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Refuses To Meet With Israeli Officials </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0903093694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0855 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0903093694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 9 Mar (MENA)--Palestinian President Yasir 
'Arafat has emphasized that he refuses to meet with any Israeli 
official under the present circumstances and until the 
consequences of the massacre at the al-Ibrahimi Mosque in Hebron 
in the occupied West Bank are removed. 
  In a statement published in today's issue of the opposition 
weekly magazine AL-AHALI, 'Arafat said several attempts have 
been made to hold a meeting between him and Israeli officials, a 
lot of pressure has been applied, and international forces have 
interfered in arranging such a meeting, but he refuses until 
Israel takes specific and practical measures that show a real 
desire to safeguard the security of the Palestinian people, who 
are under occupation. 
  'Arafat stressed the PLO's adherence to a peaceful solution 
and its commitment to the agreements reached so far. He also 
referred to the continuing coordination and consultations with 
Egypt on the peace process in the Middle East. 

</TEXT>

