<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Meets With Yeltsin's Special Envoy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0903094294 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 2200 GMT 8 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0903094294 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Yesterday evening Brother Abu-'Ammar, president 
of the state of Palestine and chairman of the PLO Executive 
Committee, received Viktor Vasilyev, special envoy of Russian 
President Boris Yeltsin for the Middle East peace process. 
  During the meeting, which came as a continuation of 
Palestinian-Russian contacts, a discussion took place on the 
current developments in the situation in the region, in light of 
the massacre carried out by Zionist settlers in the holy Ibrahim 
mosque against the sons of the Palestinian people. 
  The Russian envoy informed President 'Arafat of the 
viewpoints of the Russian leadership on the latest developments. 
Brother President Abu-'Ammar told the Russian envoy of all the 
developments which have taken place at the UN Security Council 
concerning the importance of international protection, the 
Jerusalem issue, and the problem of settlements and armed 
settlers, particularly the extremists among them, inside the 
Palestinian cities. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

