<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO Reportedly Orders Collection of Arms </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0603114494 Amman AKHIR KHABAR in Arabic 5-6 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN0603114494 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AKHIR KHABAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Exclusive" report] </F>
  [Text] Informed Palestinian sources have said the Tunis 
headquartered PLO leadership has issued stringent orders to its 
armed cadres in the occupied territories to collect their 
weapons and store them with reliable persons, and not to use 
them in any fashion whatsoever. 
  The instructions were issued after the PLO leadership 
received reports that some armed Fatah cadres were planning 
massive reprisals in retaliation against the Ibrahimi Mosque 
massacre. 
  Sources close to the Hamas Movement have said the 
Palestinian 
leadership hopes Hamas will not carry out any military 
operations at present, and that it will persist with the civil 
disobedience campaign, contending that military operations at 
present could undermine political gains. 
  The sources said Hamas halfheartedly responded to this 
request, but said it cannot restrain its cadres inside the 
occupied territories due to the monstrosity of the [Hebron] 
massacre. 

</TEXT>

