<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin, 'Arafat Hold Telephone Conversation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0903054794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0500 GMT 9 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0903054794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin yesterday held a 
telephone conversation with PLO Chief Yasir 'Arafat. This was 
the two men's second telephone conversation in two days. 
  Our political correspondent Shlomo Raz reports that the talk 
was held following a consultation held at the prime minister's 
office, in which an effort was made to draft answers to the 
PLO's queries, which had been presented as a precondition for 
renewing the negotiations. 
  Our correspondent adds that the appropriate conditions for 
resuming the negotiations have not been created as yet, but 
there is satisfaction in Jerusalem about the renewal of a direct 
link with the PLO. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

