<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin Urges Syria, Lebanon To Calm Region </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0803173994 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Arabic 1700 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0803173994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Arabic 1700 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin by Eli Nisan at </F>
the Knesset on 8 March -- recorded in Hebrew with Arabic 
subtitles; translated from the Hebrew] 
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] [Nisan] How will yesterday's 
terror attack against the SLA [South Lebanese Army] soldiers 
affect the status of the SLA and the security zone? 
  [Rabin] We have no intention of letting these incidents go 
unnoticed. We will take steps when we see fit in order to 
prevent the recurrence of such incidents. Those who perpetrated 
the attacks will be punished. 
  [Nisan] Are you now sending signals to those who perpetrated 
the attacks? 
  [Rabin] I am not sending any signals. We are in a state of 
war and not a dialogue with Hizballah and the Palestinian 
rejectionist terror organizations. On the other hand, there is 
no doubt that the Lebanese and Syrian Governments must do their 
share in calming the situation if they ever wish to promote the 
peace process. 

</TEXT>

