<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Factional Clashes Continue in Kabul, Konduz </TI></H3>
<H4>   Heavy Fighting in Kabul </H4>
<F P=102> LD0803162594 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1530 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0803162594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The capital city of Afghanistan, Kabul, was today 
the arena of heavy fire exchange among the warring factions. 
The fire exchange killed or wounded dozens of people. Several 
rockets landed near a mosque in a north-western district of 
Kabul, where the food consignment dispatched by the UN was being 
distributed, killing at least six people and wounding 30 others. 
  At dawn this morning, the exchange of fire between the 
supporters of Prime Minister Golboddin Hekmatyar and President 
Borhanoddin Rabbani, in the eastern and southern suburbs of 
Kabul, left several casualties. 

</TEXT>

