<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Policeman Wounded by Shots Near Gaza Strip </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0703082194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0700 GMT 7 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0703082194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shots were fired at a police car this morning near 
the Kisufim checkpoint at the entrance to the Gaza Strip. Our 
correspondent Nisim Qeynan reports that one of the policemen was 
slightly wounded by glass splinters and received medical 
treatment on the spot. 
  Our correspondent reports that a police car on the way to 
the 
Kisufim checkpoint spotted a suspicious-looking car driving out 
of an orchard. When the policemen ordered the driver to stop, 
he opened fire at them from an automatic weapon. The policemen 
fired back, shattering the car's back window, but it sped off 
toward Khan Yunus. Army and police forces are now searching the 
area. 

</TEXT>

