<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Receives `Urgent' Message From Yeltsin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1003092194 Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0700 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1003092194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yesterday evening President Yasir 'Arafat received 
an urgent message from the Russian administration conveyed to 
him by an envoy of Russian President Yeltsin. 
  The Russian leadership's message to 'Arafat came a few hours 
after the issuing of the Russian proposal in Moscow calling for 
the convening of a second international conference, similar to 
the Madrid conference, to activate the peace process after the 
Hebron massacre. But Israel was swift to express its opposition 
to this proposal and its preference for continuing the bilateral 
talks. The United States affirmed the same stance. 

</TEXT>

