<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Territories' Losses From Closure Estimated </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0903161194 Jerusalem AL-QUDS in Arabic 9 Mar 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> TA0903161194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-QUDS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Sa'id 'Iyad] </F>
  [Excerpt] Bethlehem -- An economic expert has estimated the 
losses to the Palestinian economy from the ongoing military 
closure and curfew imposed on the occupied territories 12 days 
ago at $50 million. 
  Dr. Nabil Kawkali, a Hebron University researcher, said that 
the economic losses cover all productive, consumer, social, 
cultural, and tourist sectors. If the military closure 
continues for a longer period, the losses will increase. He 
added that the labor and commercial sectors have suffered the 
most, because transfers of goods between the Palestinian 
occupied territories or with Israel have stopped. The 
agricultural sector comes next, as the military closure has 
compounded the losses of farmers, who have been suffering from 
consecutive losses. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-13141 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes047dd_94010" </HT>


