<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Indian Forces Fire Across Control Line; 1 Killed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1003104894 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1000 
GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1003104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Azad Kashmir, one woman was killed and two young 
men were seriously wounded as a result of shooting by Indian 
forces from across the Line of Control. According to reports, 
Indian forces started firing indiscriminately without 
provocation at Chhatri village of Kot Katahra Sector at 1400 on 
9 March. Two bullets hit the woman in the stomach, killing her 
on the spot. In two separate incidents, Indian forces fired at 
Baiwal village of Nakial Sector and Jagal village of Kot Katahra 
Sector, seriously wounding two young men. 

</TEXT>

