<F P=102>  TA0903202194 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1800 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0903202194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1800 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russia is calling for the convening of a second 
Madrid conference to rescue the peace process in the wake of the 
Hebron massacre, the INTERFAX news agency, quoting Russia's 
Deputy Foreign Minister Igor Ivanov, reported tonight. 
  Our Arab affairs correspondent Ehud Ya'ari reports that the 
move came as a surprise, has not been coordinated with the 
United States, and clashes with the U.S. Administration's effort 
to renew the process. 
  Our political correspondent Gadi Sukenik reports that 
Jerusalem rejects the idea and stresses that only the format 
decided on in the original Madrid conference is the framework 
for negotiations. 
  [Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew at 2000 GMT on 9 March in 
a 
similar report adds: "The Foreign Ministry in Jerusalem said in 
reaction that Israel rejects the proposal to reconvene the 
Madrid conference, because it has gone a long way in the 
bilateral peace talks, but adds that if Russia raises an 
official proposal on the matter, Israel will look into it and 
respond accordingly."] 

</TEXT>

