<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Compensation Agreement Reached for Hebron Victims </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0703055394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0500 GMT 7 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0703055394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Finance Ministry and National Insurance Institute 
officials have reached agreement on compensation to the victims 
of the Hebron massacre. Unmarried men who were badly injured or 
the family of a bachelor who was killed will receive 85,000 
shekels. Payments to the families of married men will range 
from 120,500 shekels to a maximum of 210,000 for those with six 
children or more. Those who suffered less severe injuries will 
receive lesser sums. The compensation agreement still needs to 
be approved by Finance Minister Shohat. 

</TEXT>

