<H3> <TI>   Hamas Squad, Rioters Arrested in East Jerusalem </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0803180594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1600 GMT 8 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0803180594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Last week the Jerusalem District police arrested 
three East Jerusalem Arabs affiliated with Hamas [Islamic 
Resistance Movement]. The three had planned to stab Jews and 
stage a big terror attack in downtown Jerusalem. Our police 
affairs correspondent Aviv Bushinsky reports that the three 
admitted they had planned to stab a settler, a policeman, or a 
soldier and that they had thrown stones at policemen and 
worshipers at the Western Wall. The police investigation 
revealed that 24-year old Jamal Basti and his two cohorts, whose 
names were banned from publication, had planned to steal an 
Israeli car and use it to smuggle arms out of Tulkarm in order 
to stage a terror attack in Israel. The Jerusalem Magistrates 
Court remanded the three in custody until the end of legal 
proceedings. 

</TEXT>

