<F P=101> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Radio Reports on Postponement of UN's Kashmir Resolution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0903153994 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1430 
GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0903153994 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Voting on Pakistan's resolution on Kashmir at the 
UN Human Rights Commission session at Geneva today has been 
postponed until 1930 this evening to allow time for further 
consultations. The postponement was sought by Pakistan. Reports 
say that Islamabad is under pressure from some Islamic 
Conference Organization -- ICO -- countries, notably Iran, to 
withdraw the resolution. As the commission took up voting on 
Pakistan's resolution early during the day, the chairman 
informed the house that Pakistani and Iranian delegations have 
sought postponement of the vote. 

</TEXT>

