<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Statement Notes `Positive' Moves of Military Units </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0903211694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2012 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0903211694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Higher Military Committee held a meeting in 
Sanaa today and discussed the results of the work of the 
military subcommittees, which are overseeing the return of the 
military units to their permanent camps before the recent 
crisis. The committee then issued the following statement: 
  The Higher Military Committee is pleased to announce to the 
brother citizens that the military commands' response to the 
committee's decision was very positive. The military units 
completed their withdrawal from the Ta'izz, Lahij, Ibb, Bab El 
Mandeb, Ma'rib, Shabwah, and Abyan Governorates. The withdrawal 
of units toward al-Bayda' and Mukayris also began last night. 
The return of the units to their previous positions is expected 
to be completed within the next 24 hours. 
  The Higher Military Committee, while stressing that the 
spirit of accord, the atmosphere of detente, and the eagerness 
to maintain the unity of the Armed Forces have prevailed in the 
circles of all the sons of the Armed Forces, appeals to the 
political leaders and the military commanders to preserve these 
achievements, which have satisfied the citizens, and to work to 
move to the second stage to apply the provisions of the accord 
document pertaining to the Armed Forces. 
  On this occasion, the Military Committee thanks the 
political 
leadership, the military commanders, and the sons of the Armed 
Forces for their cooperation and their response to the committee 
out of their national sense and their eagerness to maintain the 
safety and unity of the dear Yemeni soil. Blessed 'Id and many 
happy returns. 

</TEXT>

