<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Reportedly Launches Attacks in South </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0903201394 Tehran IRNA in English 1956 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0903201394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Dezful, Khuzestan Prov., March 9, IRNA -- The Iraqi 
Army has killed scores of inhabitants of the southern marshlands 
and destroyed at least 167 houses in the area in fresh attack, 
sources close to the Iraqi mujahidin said here today. They said 
the Iraqi Army had also levelled 15 more houses in the area 
between al-Amara and Basra. Two Iraqi students were killed at a 
school in the area as a result of the attack, they added. 
  The sources said the Iraqi regime deployed its divisions 18 
and 19, armoured division six and mechanized division 25 as well 
as its elite forces and even the riot police for the attack. 

</TEXT>

