<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   SAIRI Appeals to UN To End Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0903202594 Kuwait KSC Television in Arabic 1900 GMT 9 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0903202594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KSC Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ayatollah Sayyid Muhammad Baqir al-Hakim, chairman 
of the Supreme Assembly of the Islamic Revolution in Iraq 
[SAIRI], today appealed to the United Nations to intervene 
immediately to stop the large-scale attack which massive forces 
belonging to the Iraqi regime have been launching on al-Ahwar 
marshes in southern Iraq since 3 March. 
  Muhammad Baqir al-Hakim said that the forces of that regime 
were using internationally banned napalm incendiary bombs in 
their attacks on the people of the marshes. 
  The Iraqi opposition leader pointed out that four armored 
and 
infantry divisions were taking part in this attack supported by 
forces from the Republican Guard for intervention whenever it 
was necessary. 
  Baqir al-Hakim called on the United Nations to put pressure 
on the Iraqi regime to implement the UN Security Council's 
resolution No. 688 which stipulates stopping the policy of 
repression against the civilian population in southern Iraq. 
  Reports coming from inside Iraq mentioned that tens of 
civilians were killed or wounded in these operations, while 
hundreds of others ran away into the marshes fleeing the 
bombardment of the Iraqi regime's forces. 

</TEXT>

