<H3> <TI>   Germany Envoy, Finance Minister Discuss Expansion of Ties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0903200194 Tehran IRNA in English 1930 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0903200194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, March 9, IRNA -- Finance Minister Morteza 
Mohammad-Khani and German Ambassador to Tehran Reinhold Schenk 
here today emphasized the need for expansion of mutual 
cooperation in the areas of trade, joint ventures and transfer 
of technology. 
  Mohammad-Khani elaborating on the payment of the Iranian 
debts to Germany said Iran is interested to use technical 
assistance of the friendly countries including Germany. 
  He also expressed hope that Germany would purchase a higher 
volume of the Iranian non-oil commodities. 
  Schenk in reply said his country is also keen to expand its 
political, economic and cultural ties with Iran. 
  Establishment of a German language training center which 
would be affiliated to the Irano-German Chamber of Commerce, 
would pave the way for the expansion of cultural and trade 
relations between the two countries, he added. 

</TEXT>

