<H3> <TI>   Islamic Front, Arab Party Pledge To Foil Normalization </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0603095394 Amman AL-ASWAQ in Arabic 6 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> JN0603095394 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-ASWAQ </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The leaders of the Islamic Action Front and the 
Pan-Arab Action Front Party issued a joint statement yesterday 
unifying their positions on promoting common action to face the 
imperialist-Zionist onslaught and crystallize a plan to set up 
an Arab and Islamic front. 
  The two parties pledged to work together to foil all 
policies 
and programs promoting capitulation, particularly since these 
policies are hostile to the the Arab nation's and the Islamic 
people's right to independence, to a decent life, and to 
struggle to defeat the aggression that targets the nation's 
existence and honor. 
  The two parties also asserted the need to unify all 
national, 
pan-Arab, and Islamic forces and mobilize all the resources of 
the masses of our nation in the Arab and Islamic arenas to 
oppose all forms of capitulation and normalization. 
  They decided to form a joint committee to devise a mechanism 
of action, care for the affairs of citizens, and work to 
safeguard national unity and enhance cohesion between the sons 
of the homeland. 

</TEXT>

