<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Saratoga Missiles Spread Residual Radiation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0803134394 Amman AL-BILAD in Arabic 9 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN0803134394 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-BILAD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Confirmed information obtained by AL-BILAD says the 
nuclear radiation registered periodically since the Gulf war 
came from a U.S. aircraft carrier, the Saratoga. 
  Indubitable sources said a story that the radiation resulted 
from a defect in the Israeli Dimona nuclear reactor was leaked 
by U.S. circles to counter suspicions about the Saratoga by 
blaming the radiation on the Dimona reactor. 
  AL-BILAD obtained the following story on how this radiation 
occurred: The cruise missiles the Saratoga fired at Iraq from 
the Red Sea previously carried nuclear warheads designed to 
strike at the Warsaw Pact states. When the Gulf crisis erupted, 
the nuclear warheads were removed and replaced with conventional 
warheads, but the missiles were still charged with nuclear 
radiation, which has been registered more than once. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

