<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israeli Knesset Member on Official Visit to Syria </TI></H3>
<H4>   Comments on Meeting </H4>
<F P=102> TA0903173094 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1700 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0903173094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Israeli Arab delegation today conferred with 
Syrian President Hafiz al-Asad in Damascus. At the end of the 
meeting, the spokesman for the president's bureau said that 
al-Asad thanked the members of the delegation for sharing his 
grief and for their sincere condolences. A short time ago, our 
correspondent 'Ofer Vardi spoke with Knesset Member 
'Abd-al-Wahhab Darawshah, the head of the delegation: 
  [Begin Darawshah recording] It was a good, interesting, and 
lengthy meeting which lasted over two hours. The president 
greeted us with manifest warmth and modesty. Despite the grief 
over the death of his son, he gave us an extraordinary 
reception. He stood up and kissed each one of us, and upon our 
departure he walked me out of the hall and bid farewell to each 
of us. 
  In the meeting, we extended our condolences and discussed 
the 
peace process. He lectured us at length about the Syrian 
position on the peace process. He also welcomed our initiative 
to come to Syria to extend our condolences, and said he regarded 
us as part of the Arab world. At the same time, he emphasized 
that Syria's strategy is one of peace. 
  He said: We are prepared to embrace the formula of full 
peace in exchange for full withdrawal, and we already know what 
kind of peace we want. We want full peace in all its senses, 
but the Israeli Government has not yet defined the kind of 
withdrawal it has in mind. The prime minister speaks about a 
withdrawal on the Golan, rather than from the entire Golan. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

