<H3> <TI>   Ministry Announces Accords on Visa Exemptions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0803173394 Jerusalem GOVERNMENT PRESS OFFICE in English 8 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0803173394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem GOVERNMENT PRESS OFFICE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Issued by the Interior Ministry through spokesman Tova </F>
Elinson] 
  [Text] From the beginning of this month, Israeli citizens 
are exempt from the requirement to obtain entry visas to France; 
thus, the French Government's unilateral restriction is 
cancelled. 
  Similarly, Israel has signed mutual visa exemption 
agreements 
with the governments of Argentina, Hungary, Slovenia, Spain, and 
Portugal. 

