<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Kuwait </F>
<H3> <TI>   Envoy Calls for Maintaining Iraqi Sanctions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0803215894 Kuwait KSC Television in Arabic 1900 GMT 8 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0803215894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KSC Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Kuwait's permanent representative at the United 
Nations, Ambassador Muhammad 'Abdallah Abu al-Hasan, has warned 
against the Iraqi regime's recent maneuvres to get around the UN 
Security Council resolutions, particularly Resolution 786, to 
benefit from the lifting of the oil embargo imposed against it. 
Ambassador Muhammad 'Abdallah Abu al-Hasan stressed to the 
chairman of the UN Security Council, France's permanent 
representative at the UN, Jean-Bernard Merimee, the need for 
maintaining the sanctions imposed on the Iraqi regime as long as 
that regime, which was still refusing to release Kuwaiti POWs 
and detainees held in its prisons, did not recognize the 
sovereignty and independence of the State of Kuwait. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

