<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   PFLP-GC Claims Responsibility for SLA Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0803140394 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1215 GMT 8 
Mar 93 </F>

<F P=103> NC0803140394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Voice of Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine -- 
General Command [PFLP-GC] has claimed responsibility for 
yesterday's attack against a South Lebanese Army [SLA] patrol. 
The front said it killed or wounded more than 10 patrol members 
in al-'Ayshiyah and captured four others; three of those 
captured died while the fourth survived. 
  The front's statement added that a member of the group that 
carried out the attack was wounded. Security sources in the 
border zone this morning confirmed that one of the patrol member 
is still missing. The sources admitted that three SLA members 
had been killed along with a man and his wife in the attack 
against the patrol. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

